			<!-- ABOUT JOURNAL TABS --------------- -->
			<div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="nav-page1" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="nav-tab-page1">
				<div class="hometabscontainer journalDescriptionWrp ">
					  
					 
																<div class="homepage-image">
							<img class="img-fluid" width="200" src="https://counselor.ppj.unp.ac.id/public/journals/1/journalThumbnail_en_US.jpg" alt="">
						</div>
								
											<div class="journal-description  mb-3">
							<p>Welcome to KONSELOR, where exceptional scholarly work finds a home. We urge you to submit your manuscripts, meticulously crafted in accordance with our guidelines, emphasizing methodological rigor and insightful discussion. KONSELOR ISSN <a href="https://issn.brin.go.id/terbit/detail/1180428732" target="_blank" rel="noopener">1412-9760</a> (Print) and ISSN <a href="https://issn.brin.go.id/terbit/detail/1478120749" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2541-5948</a> (Electronic) is a peer-reviewed journal published by Universitas Negeri Padang in collaboration with Indonesian Counselor Association (IKI). The journal provides a platform for the publication for monumental research, and serving individuals in a wide range of disciplines who have an interest on Counseling Psychology. The journal's objective is to fulfill this purpose through careful editorial review and publication of expert work, by creating legitimate dialogue in a field where a diversity of opinion exists, and by providing a professional forum for interaction of these views. <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1WvTFi_EUtS6lfCRFz86qqeOqJj0oNcMk/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>This journal has been accredited by the Indonesian Ministry of Research, Technology and Higher Education (SK No: 0173/C3/DT.05.00/2025, 21 March 2025 -- Sinta 2).</strong></a></p>
							
						</div>
										
					 
						<div class="additional_content">
							<p style="text-align: justify;">At KONSELOR, we uphold a standard of scholarly excellence that demands methodological precision and thoughtful analysis in manuscripts. We provide a seamless submission experience through our user-friendly online platform, allowing authors to showcase their rigorous research and collaborate efficiently. Publishing with us signifies more than mere recognition; it signifies becoming part of a community-driven initiative dedicated to fostering collaboration and promoting open education.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">We champion the democratization of knowledge, transcending institutional constraints. Your work not only contributes to academic discourse but also becomes a catalyst for interdisciplinary dialogue, engaging a diverse readership. Through our Creative Commons licensing, you retain control over your intellectual property while sharing your contributions widely, ensuring the impactful dissemination of your research.<br /><br />KONSELOR is published quarterly, in <span style="color: #3366ff;">March, June, September,</span> and <span style="color: #3366ff;">December</span>. Authors are urged to meticulously align their submissions with the journal's <a href="https://counselor.ppj.unp.ac.id/index.php/konselor/fns" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Focus and Scope</a> to ensure relevance and suitability for publication.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Choosing KONSELOR means joining a scholarly movement committed to advancing knowledge for the greater good. By embracing our platform, you actively contribute to preventing intellectual duplication, promoting open educational resources, and ensuring equitable knowledge access globally. We eagerly anticipate welcoming your impactful research, nurturing a mutually enriching academic partnership that elevates the academic landscape. Join us in the pursuit of scholarly excellence and intellectual exchange, making a meaningful impact on the world of knowledge dissemination.</p>
						</div>
									</div>
			</div>

			<!-- LATEST ISSUE TABS --------------- -->
			<div class="tab-pane fade" id="nav-page2" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="nav-tab-page2">
													<div class="current_issue">
						<div class="reItem thumbnail"><div class="rowr"><div class="rw_issue_cover thumbnail"><div class="rw_issue_cover"><a href="https://counselor.ppj.unp.ac.id/index.php/konselor/issue/view/14" class="link"><img class="image" src="https://counselor.ppj.unp.ac.id/public/journals/1/cover_issue_14_en_US.png"></a></div></div><div class="rw_issue_description"><h1 class="current_issue_title">Vol. 14 No. 4 (2025): KONSELOR</h1><div class="current_issue_date">Published : 31 December 2025</div><div class="description"><div class="description_text2"><p>This issue of <em>KONSELOR</em> brings together a carefully curated collection of empirical and review studies that advance contemporary scholarship in guidance and counseling across developmental, educational, digital, and relational domains. The articles in this volume reflect a shared commitment to methodological rigor, contextual relevance, and the application of evidence-based approaches to support human development and well-being.</p>
<p>The issue opens with “Socio-Demographic Factors Shaping Parental Awareness of Children’s Positive Self-Concept Development,” which examines how parental awareness is shaped by socio-demographic characteristics, highlighting the central role of family context in early psychosocial development. This is followed by “Self-Control and Digital Well-Being Among University Students,” which employs a mediation analysis to position online mindfulness within a self-regulation framework, offering insights into students’ digital well-being. Building on this theme, “Effectiveness of Mindfulness-Based Cognitive Counseling Integrated with Construal Level Theory” provides empirical evidence for an integrative counseling approach aimed at enhancing university students’ mental health.</p>
<p>At the relational level, “Psychological Interventions for Enhancing Marital Commitment: A Systematic Review” synthesizes existing intervention studies and identifies key methodological strengths and limitations, contributing to the advancement of marital counseling research. The issue concludes with “Profiling Creative Competence, Cultural Literacy, and Career Readiness among Guidance and Counseling Students,” which presents a comprehensive profile to inform the development of a digital-art and local-wisdom-based learning model for counselor education.</p>
<p>The editors would like to express their sincere appreciation to all authors for their valuable contributions and to the reviewers for their rigorous, constructive, and timely evaluations, which have been instrumental in maintaining the scholarly quality of this issue. Gratitude is also extended to the editorial team for their dedication and professionalism throughout the review and publication process.</p><span class="three_dots d-none">...</span><a class="more_button" href="https://counselor.ppj.unp.ac.id/index.php/konselor/issue/view/14"><strong>More</strong></a></div></div></div></div></div>
						
						
<div class="obj_issue_toc">
	
	 	
			<div class="published d-none">
			<span class="date_label">
				Published
			</span>
			<span class="date_format">
			    
					31 December 2025
			</span>
		</div>
	
		
				<div class="issue_heading d-none">
						<div class="flex_container description_cover">
									<div class="description">
						<h2 class="description_label">##plugins.themes.themeSeventeen.issueDescription##</h2>
																			<div class="description_text">
								<p>This issue of <em>KONSELOR</em> brings together a carefully curated collection of empirical and review studies that advance contemporary scholarship in guidance and counseling across developmental, educational, digital, and relational domains. The articles in this volume reflect a shared commitment to methodological rigor, contextual relevance, and the application of evidence-based approaches to support human development and well-being.</p>
<p>The issue opens with “Socio-Demographic Factors Shaping Parental Awareness of Children’s Positive Self-Concept Development,” which examines how parental awareness is shaped by socio-demographic characteristics, highlighting the central role of family context in early psychosocial development. This is followed by “Self-Control and Digital Well-Being Among University Students,” which employs a mediation analysis to position online mindfulness within a self-regulation framework, offering insights into students’ digital well-being. Building on this theme, “Effectiveness of Mindfulness-Based Cognitive Counseling Integrated with Construal Level Theory” provides empirical evidence for an integrative counseling approach aimed at enhancing university students’ mental health.</p>
<p>At the relational level, “Psychological Interventions for Enhancing Marital Commitment: A Systematic Review” synthesizes existing intervention studies and identifies key methodological strengths and limitations, contributing to the advancement of marital counseling research. The issue concludes with “Profiling Creative Competence, Cultural Literacy, and Career Readiness among Guidance and Counseling Students,” which presents a comprehensive profile to inform the development of a digital-art and local-wisdom-based learning model for counselor education.</p>
<p>The editors would like to express their sincere appreciation to all authors for their valuable contributions and to the reviewers for their rigorous, constructive, and timely evaluations, which have been instrumental in maintaining the scholarly quality of this issue. Gratitude is also extended to the editorial team for their dedication and professionalism throughout the review and publication process.</p>
